text: The 2019–20 Austrian Cup was the 85th edition of the national cup in Austrian football. Red Bull Salzburg were the defending champions. ==Round dates== Round Match date Round 1 19 - 21 Juli 2019 Round 2 24-25 September 2019 Round 3 29-30 October 2019 Quarter-finals 7 -9 February 2020 Semi-finals 4-5 March 2020 Final 29 May 2020 == First round == Thirty-two first round matches were played between 19 and 21 July 2019. ==Second round== Sixteen second round matches were played between 24 and 25 September 2019 . ==Third round== Eight third round matches were played between 29 and 30 October 2019. ==Quarter- finals== The four quarter-finals were played between 7 and 9 February 2020. ==Semi-finals== The two semi-final matches were played on 4 and 5 March 2020. ==Final== {| style="font-size: 90%" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" GK 1 Cican Stankovic RB 5 Albert Vallci CB 15 André Ramalho CB 39 Maximilian Wöber LB 17 Andreas Ulmer (c) CM 4 Majeed Ashimeru CM 16 Zlatko Junuzović RM 77 Noah Okafor LM 14 Dominik Szoboszlai CF 20 Patson Daka CF 9 Hwang Hee-chan Substitutes: Substitutes: Substitutes: GK 31 Carlos Miguel Coronel DF 6 Jérôme Onguéné DF 25 Patrick Farkas MF 28 Antoine Bernède FW 7 Sékou Koïta FW 8 Mërgim Berisha FW 27 Karim Adeyemi Manager: Manager: Manager: Jesse Marsch Jesse Marsch Jesse Marsch Jesse Marsch ==Top goalscorers== Rank Player Club Goals 1 Ronivaldo SC Austria Lustenau 7 2 Shon Weissman Wolfsberger AC 5 2 Daniel Maderna SKU Amstetten 5 2 Dominik Weiss FC Gleisdorf 09 5 5 5 players 5 players 4 ==References== Category:Austrian Cup Category:2019–20 in European football Category:2020 in Austria Category:2010s in Austrian sport
